        </div>
        <p>
         You have not felt softness until you use a Turkish bath towel after your bath or shower. The most expensive hotels in the world only use Turkish bath towels to pamper its patrons each and every time they have an overnight stay.
         <a href="http://www.turkishtowelcompany.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="The Turkish Towel Company">
          The Turkish Towel Company
         </a>
         makes the same towel available to you.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="http://www.jennsblahblahblog.com/pamper-lavishness-turkish-bath-towel/" title="Pamper Yourself in the Lavishness of a Turkish bath Towel">
          Pamper Yourself in the Lavishness of a Turkish bath Towel
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         I dont know about your household, but our bath towels are just the run of the mill discount store towels that are rough. Over time they have lost their softness from continuous laundering and probably from the various laundry detergents that have been used over the years.
        </p>
        <p>
         The Turkish Towel Company gave me the opportunity to review some of their soft towels. I received a Bath towel, Hand Towel, Wash Cloth, all in the color of plum, 2 makeup washcloths and a pair of Turkish slippers.
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
         <a href="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items.jpg">
          <img alt="review items" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-37259" height="525" src="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items-700x525.jpg" width="700"/>
         </a>
         The Turkish Towel Company towels, washcloth and slippers
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          WOW! These towels are the softest towels I have ever felt and yes you can lose yourself in pure luxury. Just pop out of the shower and wrap yourself up and there ya go, you could just wear the towel all day because it is so soft you forget you have it on. The Turkish Towel Company has available shower wraps, Kimonos, and robes just for after shower usage.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          I was excited when I seen the makeup cloths at The Turkish Towel Company web site. When you remove your makeup usually what you take off stains your regular cloths but not with the black cloths offered by The Turkish Towel Company. Because the washcloth is already black, you cant see those mascara or lipstick stains. Made of 60% Bamboo Rayon and 40% Turkish spun cotton these towels are antibacterial that resists mildew and are extremely absorbent. Made in Turkey and distributed in the United States.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          <a href="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items-003.jpg">
           <img alt="review items 003" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-37250" height="525" src="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items-003-700x525.jpg" width="700"/>
          </a>
          Makeup washcloths
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: left;">
         Oh! Did I mention the Turkish slippers? Once again you can pamper yourself in pure luxury when you wear the Turkish slippers. We dont take care of ourselves enough especially if you are a mom and are always on a time schedule. Got to take the kids to school or you have to go to work or the hubby needs you. So, why not pamper yourself by using luxurious towels and slippers that makes you feel like you are a goddess in paradise?
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
         <a href="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items-0014.jpg">
          <img alt="review items 001" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-37255" height="933" src="http://jennsblahblahblog.com/wp-content/uploads/review-items-0014-700x933.jpg" width="700"/>
         </a>
        </p>
        <p align="center" style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          The Turkish Towel Company features several styles such as Bamboo, which is what I received, Mini Squares, Lexi, Organic and Zenith that vary in different weights and
         </span>
         absorbency
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          . Then thecolors they offer are just as beautiful as the towels themselves. Besides the white offered, they carry the plum (pictured above) Ivory, Putty (like a tan), Peacock, and Aloe, Silver, Sand, Espresso, Ice Blue, Cobalt, and Candlelight. These colors are sure to match any bathroom/pool dcor. A really nice feature of the Bamboo towel set is -look at the picture- the bath towel has three bands, the hand towel has two bands and the washcloth has one band. Have you been half asleep and grabbed a towel for the shower only to discover you grabbed the wrong size? Now you can just make a mental note that more bands means bigger towel. Cute huh? Another nice feature on the tag of every towel is not only the washing instructions but the company name and style of towel it is. Now, that just might be for the ones I received to review but it is a nice feature in case you wish to add to your collection.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          Think about pampering yourself in the luxury of softness with
         </span>
         <a href="http://www.turkishtowelcompany.com/" rel="nofollow" style="line-height: 1.5em;" target="_blank">
          The Turkish Towel Company
         </a>
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          towels, robes and slippers available online. Check out their
         </span>
         <a href="http://www.facebook.com/turkishtowelcompany" rel="nofollow" style="line-height: 1.5em;" target="_blank">
          facebook
         </a>
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          and
         </span>
         Twitter
         <span style="line-height: 1.5em;">
          pages. The Turkish Towel Company offers affordable towels in an array of fabulous colors to match or coordinate with your bathroom making you feel like youre staying in a luxurious fancy hotel in a southern tropical island.
         </span>
        </p>
